Control integration features¶

In [9]:
hvf_hm <- function(so, feature=NULL) {
    
    # Libraries 
    library(scales)
    library(viridis)
    library(ComplexHeatmap) 
    ht_opt$message = FALSE

    # Get count matrix 
    cnt <- GetAssayData(so, assay="SCT", slot="scale.data")
    if(!is.null(feature)) {cnt <- cnt[rownames(cnt) %in% feature, ]}

    # Get cluster annotation column 
    annoation_col <- data.frame("Cluster"=so$`SCT_snn_res.0.8`)
    rownames(annoation_col) <- colnames(cnt)

    # order count matrix and annotation column by cluster id
    cnt <- cnt[, order(so$`SCT_snn_res.0.8`)]
    annoation_col <- annoation_col[order(so$`SCT_snn_res.0.8`), , drop=FALSE]

    # Scale colors 
    color_break <- seq(-max(abs(cnt)), max(abs(cnt)), 0.01)
    color_ramp <- viridis(length(color_break), option="magma")

    # Column colors 
    annotation_colors <- hue_pal()(length(unique(so$`SCT_snn_res.0.8`)))
    names(annotation_colors) <- unique(so$`SCT_snn_res.0.8`)

    heatmap_scale <- grid.grabExpr(
        draw(
            ComplexHeatmap::pheatmap(
                mat=cnt, 
                main=so$treatment[1], 
                cluster_cols=FALSE, 
                cluster_rows=TRUE, 
                show_rownames=FALSE, 
                show_colnames=FALSE, 
                cellwidth=0.05, 
                cellheight=0.1, 
                treeheight_row=0, 
                annotation_col=annoation_col, 
                annotation_names_col=FALSE,
                annotation_colors=list(Cluster=annotation_colors),
                color=color_ramp, 
                breaks=color_break, 
                border_color=NA, 
                scale="none"
            )
        )
    )
    
    return(heatmap_scale)
}

Dimensional reduction and clustering¶

In [15]:
so_int <- RunPCA(so_int, npcs=100, seed.use=random_seed, verbose=FALSE)
so_int <- FindNeighbors(so_int, dims=1:100, return.neighbor=TRUE, verbose=FALSE)
so_int <- FindClusters(so_int, algorithm=4, random.seed=random_seed, verbose=FALSE)
so_int <- RunUMAP(so_int, dims=1:100, umap.method="umap-learn", seed.use=random_seed, verbose=FALSE)
